# PHASE 2 — IMPLEMENT (fix round 1, triggered by VERIFY findings)

You are fixing a diff that already exists (`bin/cli.js` cart subcommand, `tests/cli.test.js` tests). An independent fresh-context VERIFY judge (fresh context, no knowledge of prior implementation reasoning) reviewed the diff against `.devlyn/criteria.generated.md` and found the following. Fix each one exactly; do not touch any file other than `bin/cli.js` and `tests/cli.test.js`.

## Finding 1 — HIGH, verdict-binding (must fix)
`cart.catalog-error-contract`: Catalog read and parse failures bypass the required exit-2 JSON error contract and instead produce an exit-1 Node stack trace. Evidence: `const catalog = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(catalogPath, 'utf8'));` in `runCart` is outside any error handling. A catalog read/parse failure currently throws an uncaught exception (status 1, stack trace) instead of the required single JSON error object on stderr with exit 2. Fix: wrap the catalog read+parse in the same try/catch pattern already used for the cart input file, and route failures through `failCart` with an explicit JSON error (e.g. `{error: 'invalid_catalog'}` — pick a code consistent with the existing `invalid_input`/`invalid_json` naming). This directly implements the criteria's requirement: "Parsing and file-read failures must surface as JSON errors rather than silent catches."

## Finding 2 — HIGH, verdict-binding (must fix)
`cart.validation-precedence`: SKU and quantity checks are interleaved per item in a single pass, so for a cart like `{"items":[{"sku":"MUG","qty":0},{"sku":"NOPE","qty":1}]}` the current code reports `invalid_quantity` for MUG (the first item) instead of ever reaching the unknown-SKU check for NOPE. Fix: make validation order deterministic and consistent across the whole cart: first pass over every raw item checking SKU validity (unknown SKU → `invalid_sku` immediately), second pass checking quantity validity (`invalid_quantity` immediately) while combining quantities into the map, so an unknown SKU anywhere in the cart is always caught before any quantity check runs for a later item. (Two passes over `cart.items`, not one — SKU pass fully first, then quantity+combine pass.)

## Finding 3 — MEDIUM, verdict-binding (should fix)
`cart.absent-coupon-rejected`: A cart JSON with no `coupon` key at all (i.e. `cart.coupon === undefined`, not explicit `null`) is currently rejected with `invalid_coupon`, even though the intent (coupon is optional — apply it when present, otherwise zero discount) treats null and "not present" the same way. Fix: treat `cart.coupon == null` (loose equality, matches both `null` and `undefined`) as "no coupon" everywhere, rather than the current strict `cart.coupon !== null` checks.

## Already resolved — no action needed
- `cart.help-omits-command` (LOW): already fixed by a separate SURFACE_CLOSE pass that added `cart --input PATH` to the USAGE text. Do not touch USAGE again.
- `verify.full-suite-unexercised` (LOW): an artifact of the judge's own read-only sandbox rejecting `npm test`'s temp-file/socket use; not a real defect, no action needed.

